pullRequest.body:
Added several RCLike to real coercion results to support the result that eigenvalues of a hermitian matrix belong to the real spectrum of that matrix, and included this result.

Co-Authored by @j-loreaux

style, naming, and some simplification

I think this should be written as
```suggestion
theorem ofReal_eigenvalue_mem_spectrum_toEuclideanLin (i : n) :
    hA.eigenvalues i ∈ spectrum 𝕜 (toEuclideanLin A) :=
```
where hopefully the coercion is inserted automatically
Implemented name change, but unfortunately if I remove the explicit coercion, the result won't compile.
I pushed a fix
Please use the notation for `AlgEquiv` here.
Please mention `LinearMap.toContinuousLinearMap` in the docstring as a cross-reference.
Perhaps this should be called `Module.End.toContinuousLinearMap` to match?

Thanks for all the helpful suggestions! I've changed the name to `Module.End.toContinuousLinearMap`. Should this result be moved into Algebra.Module._ , or do you think it still fits here? I'm not sure if moving this will require extra imports or other inefficiencies, but the name change makes me wonder...

This result should probably move next to `LinearMap.toContinuousLinearMap` if possible. If not, `#find_home` might have some useful suggestions as to where to put it. Certainly it should not need `RCLike`, as `LinearMap.toContinuousLinearMap` doesn't.

```suggestion
theorem eigenvalues_mem_spectrum_real (i : n) : hA.eigenvalues i ∈ spectrum ℝ A := by
```

I find this very hard to parse in my head. Does this work?
```suggestion
  AlgEquiv.spectrum_eq
    (AlgEquiv.trans
      ((toEuclideanCLM : Matrix n n 𝕜 ≃⋆ₐ[𝕜] EuclideanSpace 𝕜 n →L[𝕜] EuclideanSpace 𝕜 n) :
          Matrix n n 𝕜 ≃ₐ[𝕜] EuclideanSpace 𝕜 n →L[𝕜] EuclideanSpace 𝕜 n)
      (Module.End.toContinuousLinearMap (EuclideanSpace 𝕜 n)).symm)
    _
```
I'm not sure what this comment is suggesting, really. (Sorry, I'm new to this!) Are you suggesting a stylistic change? Does the original somehow not conform to library standard?
Yes, I think this is a style change: the idea is to reflect parenthesis nesting with indentation.
It doesn't look like you ever made this change

Is this what you meant?
```suggestion
/-- Eigenvalues of a Hermitian matrix, coerced, belong to the spectrum of the associated
`toEuclideanLin`. -/
```
Yes, thanks!

```suggestion
/-- Eigenvalues of a Hermitian Matrix, coerced, belong to the spectrum of the assoc.toEuclideanLin -/
```

```suggestion
/-- The spectrum of a Hermitian matrix `A` coincides with the spectrum of `toEuclideanLin A`. -/
```

we don't abbreviate `spectrum` to `spec` anywhere else in the library.
```suggestion
theorem spectrum_toEuclideanLin : spectrum 𝕜 (toEuclideanLin A) = spectrum 𝕜 A :=
```

Does this not work?
```suggestion
  apply spectrum.of_algebraMap_mem 𝕜
```
Will check. (I hope that it will!)
Yep.

```suggestion
    [NormedSpace 𝕜 E] [FiniteDimensional 𝕜 E] : (E →ₗ[𝕜] E) ≃ₐ[𝕜] (E →L[𝕜] E) :=
  { LinearMap.toContinuousLinearMap with
    map_mul' := fun _ _ ↦ rfl
    commutes' := fun _ ↦ rfl }
```

How do you feel about just inlining this in the proof of `eigenvalues_mem_spectrum_real` below? We can always get back easily with `spectrum.algebraMap_mem` and `spectrum_toEuclideanLin`. I just feel like we don't really need many results about `spectrum 𝕜 (toEuclideanLin A)`.

This is totally fine...I feel a bit weird about *having* these coercion-involved results, so inlining them seems better. Not sure this is the correct intuition, but...trying to learn the right design mojo...
Used apply, but I think it's probably ok.

```suggestion
/-- Eigenvalues of a hermitian matrix A are in the ℝ spectrum of A. -/
```
